    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>In the Mideast, Days of Anguish</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stuart Pilichowski letter on Palestinian terrorists striking once again at Israeli citizens going to work; says Sec Colin Powell must insist on nothing less than complete cessation of terrorist activity (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''At Least 8 Killed in Suicide Bombing on a Bus in Israel'' (front page, April 10):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''At Least 8 Killed in Suicide Bombing on a Bus in Israel'' (front page, April 10):</p>
        <p>After a relative calm in Israel since the incursion of Israeli military forces into Palestinian areas, once again terrorists have struck at Israeli citizens on their way to work.</p>
        <p>We look forward to the visit by Secretary of State Colin L. Powell to the region in the hopes that he will be able to convince Yasir Arafat that continuing terrorism will not lead to any positive conclusion for the Palestinian people.</p>
        <p>What rabbit will Secretary Powell pull out of his hat to create a new beginning? He needs to insist that the United States will stand for nothing less than a complete cessation of terrorist activity. Is that really such an unreasonable request?</p>
        <p>STUART PILICHOWSKI  Mevasseret Zion, Israel  April 10, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
